Professionals

Investment Team
John G. Prichard, CFA
John G. Prichard, CFA
Co-Founder & Principal
President
A co-founder of Knightsbridge, John serves as the Chief Investment Officer and President.  He has 20 years of investment experience. Prior to the 1998 co-founding of Knightsbridge, John worked at Canterbury Capital Services, Inc. and in the investment department of Santa Barbara Bank and Trust. He earned an MA in finance and banking from Boston University and a BA in economics from the University of California, San Diego. A CFA charterholder, John has served as President of the Orange County Society of Investment Managers (CFA Society of Orange County). He currently serves on the board of trustees of the South Coast Repertory Theatre and on the board of trustees for the Newport Beach Public Library.

Miles Yourman, CFA
Miles Yourman, CFA
Principal
Miles participates in the firm’s portfolio management and investment anomaly and equity research efforts, with an emphasis on macro analysis. After graduating from Dartmouth College with an AB in economics (Phi Beta Kappa, magna cum laude), he spent three years in New York and London working for Citigroup’s Strategy & Planning division before joining Knightsbridge.  Miles earned his MBA from Columbia Business School where he graduated with Dean's Honors and Distinction and was awarded the Sonkin Family Prize for Value Investing. Miles is a CFA charterholder.


 
Account Management Team
Teresa A. Wagner
Teresa A. Wagner
Chief Operating Officer, Chief Compliance Officer & Finance and Accounting
Teresa oversees the firm’s account management group and serves as the firm’s chief operating officer and the chief compliance officer. Prior to joining Knightsbridge, Teresa served as vice president with fund administration and compliance oversight responsibilities for Pacific Investment Management Company and PIMCO Advisors. Prior to PIMCO Advisors, she directed advisory administration and subsidiary development for Pacific Financial Asset Management Company, and worked as an analyst for Pacific Life. Teresa graduated magna cum laude with a BA in business administration from University of Phoenix.
 
 
Ivan B. Lee
Ivan B. Lee
Account Manager & Client Servicing 
Ivan is involved in client servicing, marketing, account management, and trading.  Prior to Ivan’s tenure at Knightsbridge, he spent three years at Canterbury Capital Services, Inc.  Ivan’s industry experience includes account management, investment management operations, GIPS compliance and performance measurement, portfolio reviews, and client servicing.  Ivan received his BA in economics from the University of California, Irvine.





 
