Investment Services & Portfolio Management




Company Description


Knightsbridge Asset Management seeks to perform in all market and economic environments by investing opportunistically among equities with a focus on capital preservation, as well as rate of return. The firm employs a value-oriented approach, seeking to capitalize on market inefficiencies and irrational investor behavior. The firm believes that excess returns can be generated by exploiting ‘investment anomalies’ or disruptive events believed to cause temporary undervaluation and that signal future outperformance. Knightsbridge places emphasis on absolute returns and invests opportunistically without regard to index characteristics. At times, they may use cash as a defensive tool. Portfolio holdings are diversified across market-capitalization. Stocks are purchased only when Knightsbridge believes an 80% to 100% investment return is probable over a three year holding period.




